1 aero space and aeronautics in this state and to encourage the
2 establishment of airports and air navigation facilities. It shall
3 cooperate with and assist the federal government, the municipalities
4 of this state, and other persons in the development of aerospace and
5 aeronautics, and shall seek to coordinate the aeronautical
6 activities of these bodies and persons. Municipalities are
7 authorized to cooperate with the Department in the development of
8 aeronautics and aeronautical facilities in this state.
9 B. The Department may organize and administer an aerospace and
10 aviation education program in cooperation with the schools,
11 colleges, and for the general public, and may prepare and conduct
12 voluntary flight clinics for airmen and issue such bulletins and
13 publications as may be required. This program shall be known and
14 may be cited as the “AeroSPACE Program” or “Aero Student Pathways
15 for Aerospace Careers and Education”. This program shall be a
16 partnership with primary, secondary, career technology, and higher
17 education providers to respond to the workforce needs of the
18 aviation and aerospace industry by promoting and organizing quality
19 curriculum, enhanced classroom instruction, and research-based
20 educational programs. The AeroSPACE Program shall collaborate with
21 industry and act as the facilitator for the collection and sharing
22 of information, development and implementation of activities, and
23 the dissemination of resources concerning aerospace education with
24 the primary goal being to establish a common statewide strategy for
SB730 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 impl ementing aerospace educational curriculum initiatives to better
2 prepare students for an aviation and aerospace career. The Oklahoma
3 Aeronautics Commission may employ established program processes or
4 contract with other qualified entities to operate the AeroSPACE
5 Program. The Oklahoma Aeronautics Commission may accept funding
6 that includes, but is not limited to, donations, contractual
7 arrangements, in-kind services, federal or state appropriations, and
8 grants.
9 C. The Department shall assist in all aeronautical matters
10 related to emergency management actions in conformance with federal
11 directions and with the Emergency Operations Plan of the state.
12 D. The Department may establish air markers throughout the
13 state.
14 E. The Department may purchase and install roadside signs
15 directing highway traffic to airports, subject to approval of the
16 State Transportation Commission.
17 F. The Department shall:
18 1. Draft and recommend necessary legislation to advance the
19 interests of the state in aerospace and aeronautics;
20 2. Represent the state in aeronautical matters before federal
21 agencies and other state agencies; and
22 3. Participate as party plaintiff or defendant or as intervener
23 on behalf of the state or any municipality or citizen thereof in any
