2 aeronautics.
3 G. 1. The Department shall develop and adopt a five-year
4 Airport Construction Program on an annual basis which lists federal
5 and state funding that the Department has available for the
6 development of airport infrastructure. In addition, the Department
7 shall adopt a statewide airport system plan on a regular basis which
8 details the twenty-year planning horizon for publicly owned, public-
9 use airports and sets the service level, role, and functional
10 classification of airports within the Oklahoma Airport System. The
11 system plan will be made available to the public and shall serve as
12 the Department’s official document which guides the programming of
13 public funds for airport infrastructure. An airport must be
14 included in the system plan to be eligible for funding.
15 2. The development of the five-year Airport Construction
16 Program shall begin with supporting and achieving the goals laid out
17 in the statewide airport system plan and will be guided by the air
18 transportation needs and priorities of airports within the system.
19 The basic goals within the system plan include, but are not limited
20 to, airport safety, security, infrastructure preservation and
21 sustainment, economic enhancement, capacity, meeting Federal
22 Aviation Administration (FAA) or Department standards, and pro-
23 growth development.
